<div class="UIAccountCreationWizard">
	<div class="AccountCreationStep2">
		<div class="StepInfos">
			<div class="InfoTitle">
				Step 2 : Mail Identity Settings.
			</div>
			<div>
				Mail identity is the name and emal address used in your email correspondence. Each
				mail account has an identity, which is the information comes with your outgoing
				messages that identifies you to mail recipients when the receive your mails.
				To set up your mail identities, let's enter the information in the fields below.
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<div class="UIForm StepForm">
			<div class="HorizontalLayout">
				<table class="UIFormGrid">
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td class="FieldLabel">You Outgoing Name :</td>
							<td class="FieldComponent">
								<input id="YouOutgoingName" type="text" name="YouOutgoingName"/>
							</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="FieldLabel">Email Address :</td>
							<td class="FieldComponent">
								<input id="EmailAddress" type="text" name="EmailAddress"/>
							</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="FieldLabel">Reply-to Address :</td>
							<td class="FieldComponent">
								<input id="AccountDescription" type="text" name="AccountDescription"/>
							</td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
		</div>

